commentTextItems.html: banged in short again and this time he uppercuts it over the infield to secure another whitewash for Bangladesh as New Zealand's winless streak in internationals against Bangladesh in Bangladesh extends to more than 5 years

commentPostTextItems.html: New Zealand claimed they were complacent and underprepared in 2010. This time they undertook a training camp in Sri Lanka beforehand. It's made no difference to the results as the home side sweep the visitors again, today on the back of a well-constructed run chase courtesy of Shamsur's 96 and supporting efforts from (in particular) Naeem and Nasir which meant that Ross Taylor's century and Colin Munro's aggressive 85 were in vain

Man of the Match is Shamsur Rahman and Man of the Series is Mushfiqur Rahim. Unfortunately we can't bring you the presentation so that concludes our coverage for today. Do join me on Wednesday at 1.00pm local time to see if the only Twenty20 International will bring more joy for the home side or if the visitors can finally break this losing streak in Bangladesh. Until then, this is Avi Singh thanking you for following us tonight and wishing you well wherever you are. Cheers!

commentTextItems.html: banged in on middle and beats the attempted pull
heaved off the inner edge to square leg. 3 to win off the final over

headshotImage.longCaption: Sohag Gazi  player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: half-volley outside off is drilled with excellent timing as he bisects cover and mid-off and finds the boundary

commentPostTextItems.html: Nithin Valentine: "Can Anderson pull off a Rubel esque hatrick? :-)" Wouldn't seem that way

commentTextItems.html: beaten as he fires it into leg on a good length, Gazi backs away and swings and misses
across the line heave results in a thick edge down to third man
and Mr W Ides increases his total to 9 for Bangladesh as Anderson fires this too far outside off
slides down leg and the batsman happily watches it pass him by
launches a drive on the bounce to mid-off and runs, gone by miles had the throw hit as he runs anyway
defended into the point region
excellent over for the visitors is ruined buy a long hop on off and the home side edge back in front as Nasir launches this handsomely into the stands at midwicket

commentPostTextItems.html: D/L par is 288 after 48, Bangladesh are 8 ahead

dismissalText.commentary: Ziaur Rahman c Milne b McClenaghan 22 (20b 2x4 2x6 35m) SR: 110

dismissalComment.html: charges down and attempts a big heave over midwicket, top edges it straight up and Milne settles under it uneasily before clinging on

dismissalText.commentary: Mominul Haque c & b Devcich 32 (33b 4x4 0x6 49m) SR: 96.96

dismissalComment.html: tame end to a busy innings from Mominul as he goes back to a fullish ball and tries to work it to leg but ends up playing it almost off the middle of the blade softly back to Devcich

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Taylor b McCullum 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: well-taken catch by Taylor at square leg! The crowd has fallen silent as this long hop is pulled fiercely and looks to be heading to the square leg fence but Taylor who is very close to the wicket jumps and plucks a one-handed beauty above his head in similar fashion to a catch he took to dismiss Tamim during the Test series

dismissalText.commentary: Shamsur Rahman c Ronchi b Anderson 96 (107b 7x4 4x6 145m) SR: 89.71

dismissalComment.html: out for 96! Shamsur has to go after an excellent knock, it was on a good length outside off, not quite driveable length but Shamsur threw the hands at it away from the body and got a thick edge which deviated into Ronchi's gloves

dismissalText.commentary: Naeem Islam run out (McClenaghan/Ronchi) 63 (74b 5x4 0x6 99m) SR: 85.13

dismissalComment.html: Bangladesh lose the set batsman! Had a wild slog at a ball outside off and skied it down to third man and went for a second that wasn't on, the dive can't save him as Ronchi whips the bails off

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah c Ronchi b McClenaghan 16 (13b 1x4 0x6 26m) SR: 123.07

dismissalComment.html: short on leg and he tries to scoop it fine, goes through to the keeper and all appeal, appears to have flicked the shoulder and the ball carried but after referring upstairs, the umpire has given him!
